    <!-- Why This Playbook -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-3">Why Reform, Not Just Monitoring</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Johannesburg generates nearly 16% of South Africa's GDP, yet hundreds of thousands of residents endure burst pipes, collapsing electricity grids, and dangerous roads. The City has one of the country's largest municipal budgets — and among the worst service delivery records.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Monitoring asks:</strong> Did the municipality fix the pothole?<br />
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Reform advocacy asks:</strong> Why are 40% of potholes still unrepaired after 30 days, and what must change structurally so that this is no longer possible?
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Theory of Change -->
    <details class="mb-6 group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg" open>
      <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary hover:bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <span>1. Theory of Change</span>
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4">
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Three Levels of Reform</h4>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
            <thead><tr class="bg-gray-50"><th class="text-left p-2 font-heading font-semibold border-b">Level</th><th class="text-left p-2 font-heading font-semibold border-b">What Changes</th><th class="text-left p-2 font-heading font-semibold border-b">Examples</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b"><td class="p-2 font-semibold">Policy &amp; By-law</td><td class="p-2">Written rules governing the city</td><td class="p-2">Procurement by-law, tariff schedule, IDP commitments</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b"><td class="p-2 font-semibold">Institutional</td><td class="p-2">How departments and SOEs operate</td><td class="p-2">Performance contracts, independent oversight boards, ward-level SLAs</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="p-2 font-semibold">Political &amp; Cultural</td><td class="p-2">Norms and power dynamics</td><td class="p-2">Councillor scorecards, community veto rights, anti-corruption culture</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-3 mt-4 text-sm">
          <p class="font-semibold text-amber-800">The Reform Hypothesis</p>
          <p class="text-amber-900 text-xs mt-1">IF cross-functional civil society actors build an organised, evidence-based, multi-sector coalition AND use coordinated pressure across legal, political, media, and community channels AND engage constructively with reform-minded actors inside government THEN structural reforms are adopted that improve service delivery for all residents.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Reform Pathways -->
    <details class="mb-6 group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary hover:bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <span>2. Four Reform Pathways</span>
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4">
        <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">No single pathway is sufficient. The coalition uses all four in combination:</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 p-3 bg-amber-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm">Legal Pathway</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">PAIA litigation, Public Protector complaints, Information Regulator, High Court review of procurement decisions, AGSA referrals</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 p-3 bg-amber-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm">Political Pathway</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Candidate scorecards, IDP submissions, Council deputation, public hearings, multi-party engagement, election monitoring</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 p-3 bg-amber-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm">Media &amp; Public Narrative</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Investigative partnerships, data journalism, social media campaigns, community radio, documentary evidence</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 p-3 bg-amber-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm">Inside-Outside Strategy</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Joint technical working groups, co-designing solutions, amplifying whistleblowers, shadow policy drafting</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Power Mapping -->
    <details class="mb-6 group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary hover:bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <span>3. Power Mapping Framework</span>
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <div class="rounded-lg border-2 border-emerald-300 p-3 bg-emerald-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-emerald-800">Champions</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Aligned on reform, have power to act. <strong>Strategy:</strong> activate, resource, protect.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1 italic">Reform caucus councillors, whistleblower officials, progressive SOE board members</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border-2 border-blue-300 p-3 bg-blue-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">Swing Actors</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Uncommitted, have power. <strong>Strategy:</strong> persuade with evidence and incentives.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1 italic">Business community, faith leaders, suburban ratepayers</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border-2 border-amber-300 p-3 bg-amber-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-amber-800">Blocked Allies</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Aligned on reform, lack power. <strong>Strategy:</strong> organise and amplify.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1 italic">Resident associations, underfunded NGOs, community journalists</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border-2 border-red-300 p-3 bg-red-50">
            <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-red-800">Opponents</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Against reform or benefit from status quo. <strong>Strategy:</strong> contain, expose, neutralise.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1 italic">Patronage networks, corrupt procurement officials</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Coalition Structure -->
    <details class="mb-6 group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary hover:bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <span>4. Coalition Structure (CSRA Model)</span>
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4">
        <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3 text-sm">The CSRA is a coalition of organisations — not a new organisation itself. It operates on a federated model: member organisations retain full autonomy but commit to shared priorities and coordinated messaging.</p>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Member Categories</h4>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-sm mb-4">
